  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>parsley</strong> roughly, including the stalks</p><p>Deseed your <strong>sweet pointed pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and slice into rings</p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>butter beans</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1685517032936-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1685517032936-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1685517032936-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1685517032936-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1685517032936-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) over a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced pepper</strong> to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1685517043802-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1685517043802-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1685517043802-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1685517043802-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1685517043802-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>waxy potatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Add the <strong>halved waxy potatoes</strong> to a heatproof bowl, then cover the bowl with <strong>cling film</strong> and pierce a few holes in the top with a fork</p><p>Put the bowl in the<strong> microwave</strong> for 6-8 min or until the potatoes are fork-tender</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1685517052635-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1685517052635-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1685517052635-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1685517052635-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1685517052635-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>(save the rest for later!)<strong> </strong>to the pan with the <strong>drained butter beans</strong>, <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>ground coriander </strong>and <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong> with your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>, 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[125ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>sugar </strong>and bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to medium and cook for 5-6 min or until the vegetables are tender and the stock has thickened to a stew-like consistency</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1685517056861-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1685517056861-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1685517056861-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1685517056861-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1685517056861-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>remaining chopped garlic</strong> (not a big garlic fan? Try using less!) with your <strong>mayo</strong> in a bowl</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>pepper </strong>and stir it all together – this is your <strong>garlic aioli</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1685517060761-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1685517060761-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1685517060761-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1685517060761-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1685517060761-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once thickened, make 1 well per person in the pan, then crack your <strong>egg[s] </strong>into the well[s] and cook, covered, for 2-3 min or until the egg is done to your liking – this is your <strong>Spanish-style bean shakshuka</strong></p><p>Tip: Give your egg a little shake before you crack for a perfectly centred yolk!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1685517063931-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1685517063931-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1685517063931-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1685517063931-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1685517063931-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a separate large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) over a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>cooked potatoes </strong>to the pan cut side down and cook for 2-3 min or until golden</p><p>Once golden, add <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped parsley</strong> (you'll use the rest later) and season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up – these are your <strong>herby potatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1685517067896-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1685517067896-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1685517067896-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1685517067896-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1685517067896-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Spanish-style bean shakshuka</strong> with the <strong>herby potatoes</strong> to the side</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>remaining chopped parsley </strong>and drizzle over the <strong>garlic aioli</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
